COMMON FACILITIES LAND RIGHTS AGREEMENT
This COMMON FACILITIES LAND RIGHTS AGREEMENT (this "Agreement") is made and entered into to be effective as of December ____, 2020 (the "Effective Date"), by and between RED CLOUD WIND LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("Red Cloud"), whose address is 1088 Sansome Street, San Francisco, California 94111, Attention: General Counsel, and DURAN MESA LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("Duran Mesa"), whose address is 1088 Sansome Street, San Francisco, California 94111, Attention: General Counsel, with reference to the following recitals:
RECITALS
A. Red Cloud has acquired certain real property rights pursuant to certain land lease and easement agreements as described on Exhibit A-1 attached hereto and made a part hereof (the "Red Cloud Master Land Rights Agreements"), which encumber that certain real property located in Torrance County, State of New Mexico, all such real property as described on Exhibit B-1 attached hereto and made a part hereof (all such real property heretofore described, the "Red Cloud Property").
B. Duran Mesa has acquired certain real property rights pursuant to certain land lease and easement agreements as described on Exhibit A-2 attached hereto and made a part hereof (the "Duran Mesa Master Land Rights Agreements"), which encumber that certain real property located in Torrance County, State of New Mexico, all such real property as described on Exhibit B-2 attached hereto and made a part hereof (all such real property heretofore described, the "Duran Mesa Property").
C. The Red Cloud Master Land Rights Agreements and the Duran Mesa Master Land Rights Agreements are sometimes referred to herein collectively or respectively (as applicable given the context) as the "Master Land Rights Agreements". The Red Cloud Property and the Duran Mesa Property are sometimes referred to herein collectively or respectively (as applicable given the context) as the "Property".
D. Red Cloud, Duran Mesa and certain other parties have developed, are in the process of developing or contemplate developing wind power generation facilities and related equipment on certain real property, a portion of which is the Property (each such development owned or to be owned individually by Red Cloud, Duran Mesa or said other parties shall be referred to herein as a "Project", and the Projects together constituting the "Wind Farm Complex").
E. Red Cloud, Duran Mesa and said other parties have entered into that certain Co-Tenancy, Common Facilities and Easement Agreement dated of even date herewith (as amended, amended and restated, supplemented or otherwise modified from time to time, the "Common Facilities Agreement") with respect to their rights and responsibilities regarding the development and operation of the Wind Farm Complex and the Common Facilities Improvements (as defined below) located thereon.
F. Red Cloud and Duran Mesa intend to own an undivided interest in and to those certain improvements and other assets to be located on the Property and described in Exhibit C attached hereto (collectively, the "Common Facilities Improvements").
G. Red Cloud and Duran Mesa intend to utilize the Common Facilities in connection with the Projects pursuant to and in accordance with the Common Facilities Agreement.
H. In accordance with the Common Facilities Agreement, Red Cloud desires to grant Duran Mesa certain real property rights over and across the Red Cloud Property and Duran Mesa desires to grant Red Cloud certain real property rights over and across the Duran Mesa Property for the purpose of, among other things, accessing, developing, constructing, operating, maintaining and inspecting the Common Facilities Improvements located on the Property. Red Cloud and Duran Mesa may hereafter be referred to as, together, the "Parties" and each, a "Party". Capitalized terms not been defined herein shall have the meaning assigned to such terms in the Common Facilities Agreement.
AGREEEMENTS
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing recitals, the mutual covenants and agreements set forth herein and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt of which is hereby acknowledged, Red Cloud and Duran Mesa hereby agree as follows:
SECTION 1 - GRANT OF RIGHTS
1.1 Grant of Land Rights.
1.1.1 Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, the Common Facilities Agreement and the Red Cloud Master Land Rights Agreements, Red Cloud hereby irrevocably and unconditionally grants and conveys to Duran Mesa and its successors and assigns and Duran Mesa hereby irrevocably and unconditionally grants and conveys to Red Cloud and its successors and assigns a nonexclusive easement in, upon, over, across, along, above and under the Red Cloud Property and the Duran Mesa Property, respectively, solely for the purposes more particularly described in Section 1.2 below (collectively, the "Land Rights").
1.1.2 The term of the Land Rights shall expire, as to each portion of the Land Rights, concurrently with the expiration or earlier termination of the Master Land Rights Agreements affecting such portion of the Property.
1.2 Purposes of Land Rights. Subject to and to the extent permitted by this Agreement, the Common Facilities Agreement and the Master Land Rights Agreements, the Land Rights are intended for the following purposes and activities: (a) ingress and egress on, over and across the Property by means of any existing roads and lanes thereon, and by such other roads and lanes as the Parties may construct thereon from time to time for the purpose of accessing the Common Facilities Improvements and (b) constructing the Common Facilities Improvements in, on, over, under, along, across and within a portion of the Property, and operating, maintaining and inspecting the same, and undertaking any other activities, whether accomplished by the Parties or a third party authorized by the Parties, that the Parties determine are necessary, helpful, appropriate or convenient in connection with, incidental to or to accomplish any of the foregoing purposes.
1.3 As-Is Condition. The Land Rights are granted and conveyed to Red Cloud and Duran Mesa, respectively, subject to the present condition of the Property and on an "AS-IS" basis, and each of Red Cloud and Duran Mesa hereby accepts the Land Rights granted to it and such Red Cloud Property and Duran Mesa Property, respectively, in such condition and on such basis. Each of Red Cloud and Duran Mesa acknowledges that neither such other Party nor any of its representatives or agents has made any representation or warranty as to the suitability of the Red Cloud Property or the Duran Mesa Property, respectively, or any portion thereof for the conduct of the operations of the other Party or for any other purpose.
SECTION 2 - MISCELLANEOUS RIGHTS AND OBLIGATIONS
2.1 Indemnity. Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold the other Party and its subgrantees, heirs, successors and assigns harmless from and against any losses, damages, expenses or liabilities resulting from any action of the indemnifying Party and of any Persons (as defined in the Common Facilities Agreement) authorized by, through or under the indemnifying Party on the Property, or any part thereof or any breach of this Agreement.
2.2 Compliance with Law. Each Party shall, at its sole cost and expense, promptly comply with all applicable Laws (as defined in the Common Facilities Agreement) and with all covenants, conditions and restrictions in effect during the term of this Agreement or any part thereof regulating the use of the Property, or any facilities thereon; provided however, that such Party shall have the right to contest by appropriate legal proceedings the validity or applicability of any such Law.
2.3 Liens. Red Cloud shall pay, when due, all claims for labor or materials furnished to or on behalf of Red Cloud at or for use on the Property or any part thereof, which claims are or may be secured by any mechanic's or materialmen's lien which affect the use or enjoyment of the Land Rights. Duran Mesa shall pay, when due, all claims for labor or materials furnished to or on behalf of Duran Mesa at or for use on the Property or any part thereof, which claims are or may be secured by any mechanics' or materialmen's lien which affects the use or enjoyment of the Land Rights.
2.4 Right To Assign and Encumber. Neither Party shall, at any time and from time to time, without obtaining the other Party's consent, (a) transfer, assign, alienate, license or grant all or any portion of its right, title or interest under this Agreement (including by grant of co-tenancy interest or grant of subeasement) to any Person, except as provided in the Common Facilities Agreement, and/or (b) hypothecate, mortgage or pledge all or any portion of its right, title or interest under this Agreement, except as provided in the Common Facilities Agreement.
2.5 Land Rights Subordinate to Master Land Rights Agreements. Notwithstanding anything that may be construed to the contrary herein, this Agreement, and all of the rights of the Parties hereunder, are and shall at all times be subject and subordinate to the Master Land Rights Agreements. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, and notwithstanding anything that may be construed to the contrary in this Agreement:
2.5.1 This Agreement does not and shall not grant to any Party any rights, interests or benefits greater than those provided to or permitted to such Party under the Master Land Rights Agreements; and this Agreement shall in all respects be limited by and taken subject to the terms, conditions and provisions of the Master Land Rights Agreements. Each of Red Cloud and Duran Mesa represents and warrants that this Agreement, and the granting of rights, interests and benefits hereunder, do not contravene, conflict with or result in a breach of, or require any consent under any of the Red Cloud Master Land Rights Agreements or the Duran Mesa Master Land Rights Agreements, respectively, other than any consent obtained prior to the date hereof.
2.5.2 The Parties shall not take or fail to take any action, where such action or failure would constitute a default under, or would be inconsistent with the terms and provisions of, any of the Master Land Rights Agreements; and the Parties shall at all times comply with such terms and provisions.
2.5.3 In the event that the terms, conditions or obligations set forth in this Agreement are inconsistent with or contradict the terms, conditions or obligations set forth in the Master Land Rights Agreements, then this Agreement shall control over the Master Land Rights Agreements to the extent that this Agreement conveys fewer rights or benefits, or imposes greater limitations, requirements or obligations on a Party; otherwise the terms, conditions and obligations set forth in the Master Land Rights Agreements shall control.
2.5.4 Each of the Parties hereby assumes and agrees to perform all obligations of such Party under the respective Master Land Rights Agreements that are applicable to, and that would bind such Party in connection with, the operations of the other Party on the Property.
2.6 Rights of the Parties With Respect to the Property.
2.6.1 Each Party shall have the right to undertake only those activities on the Property that are contemplated by the Common Facilities Agreement or this Agreement and that are permitted by the Master Land Rights Agreements.
2.6.2 Red Cloud hereby reserves the right to undertake any activities on the Red Cloud Property that are permitted by the Red Cloud Master Land Rights Agreements and Duran Mesa hereby reserves the right to undertake any activities on the Duran Mesa Property that are permitted by the Duran Mesa Master Land Rights Agreements including the right to (a) build and operate wind power generating facilities and projects, (b) enter into subeasements or subleases, easements, licenses, co-tenancy agreements and other agreements with other Persons and (c) use and cross the Property, and grant or assign such use and crossing rights (or undivided or subordinate interests therein) to other Persons. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, each of Red Cloud and Duran Mesa may grant and convey non-exclusive subeasements over the Red Cloud Property or the Duran Mesa Property, respectively, in favor of other Persons for any of the purposes provided in the respective Master Land Rights Agreements in each case together with (i) all necessary or appropriate rights of way for access, ingress and egress to and from the respective Property and (ii) the right in the transferee to grant or convey undivided or subordinate interests therein to other Persons.
2.6.3 Each Party reserves the right, in its discretion, to amend, supplement or restate one or more of its Master Land Rights Agreements without the consent of the other Party, and the Parties hereby agree (a) to each such amendment, supplement and restatement and (b) that any such amendment, supplement or restatement shall automatically, and without the need for further documentation, be senior to the Land Rights and the rights of the Parties under this Agreement; provided, however, that no such amendment, supplement or restatement shall have the effect of (i) materially increasing the duties or obligations of the Parties under this Agreement, (ii) materially decreasing the rights or benefits given or afforded to the Parties or the Lenders hereunder or (iii) impairing the security of any Lender's lien. The Parties shall deliver a copy of each such amendment, supplement and restatement to the other and each Lender immediately after the same has been executed.
2.7 Performance of Obligations. Each Party hereby covenants that it will (a) perform its obligations under each of its respective Master Land Rights Agreements in all material respects and (b) notwithstanding any provision of such respective Master Land Rights Agreements that would allow such Party to quitclaim or surrender the same or any portion thereof, either (at such Party's sole discretion) (i) keep and maintain each of its respective Master Land Rights Agreements in full force and effect for the full term thereof or (ii) quitclaim the same to the other Party.
2.8 Conduct. Each Party shall (a) conduct or cause to be conducted its operations and activities on the Property and each part thereof in accordance with sound and prudent engineering, operation and maintenance practices and (b) keep its facilities in good condition and repair, in good and efficient working order and in a clean, sanitary and safe condition. Neither Party shall conduct its operations or activities, or use or permit the use of the Property or any part thereof or its facilities in any manner that will create waste or cause a nuisance or that will damage the Property or any part thereof; and each Party shall be liable and responsible to the other Party for any such waste, nuisance or damage.
2.9 Restoration. Within six (6) months after the expiration or earlier termination of this Agreement, if either Party fails to perform the removal and restoration obligations under one or more of its Master Land Rights Agreements, the other Party or its or other designees shall have the right but not the obligation to undertake restoration and removal activities, and shall have a continuing subeasement to enter the Property for such purpose during such six (6)-month period.
2.10 Ownership of Improvements. The Parties acknowledge and agree that (a) each Party's facilities are and shall be and remain severable and separable from the Property, (b) except as provided herein, neither Party shall have any ownership or other interest in any facilities (other than the Common Facilities Improvements) installed or placed on the Property of the other Party as separate property by such other Party, and either Party may remove any or all such facilities owned by such Party at any time and from time to time, (c) to the extent permitted by Law, each of Red Cloud and Duran Mesa hereby waives any statutory or common law lien that it might otherwise have in or to the facilities or any thereof that are owned separately and not as tenants in common with each other and (d) if such waiver is not enforceable or permitted by Law, then each of Red Cloud and Duran Mesa hereby subordinates each such statutory or common law lien to any Lender's lien from time to time existing against such facilities or any thereof.

TRANSMISSION EASEMENT AGREEMENT
THIS TRANSMISSION EASEMENT AGREEMENT ("Agreement"), is executed effective this _____ day of [_____], 2020, by and between Red Cloud Wind LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("Grantor"), whose address is 1088 Sansome Street, San Francisco, CA 94111, Attn: General Counsel, and [Tecolote Wind LLC][Duran Mesa LLC], a Delaware limited liability company ("Grantee"), whose address is 1088 Sansome Street, San Francisco, CA 94111, Attn: General Counsel. Grantor and Grantee may hereafter be referred to as, together, the "Parties" and each, a "Party". PREMISES A. Grantor holds certain leasehold and easement rights pursuant to those certain leases and easement agreements as more particularly described on Exhibit A attached hereto and made a part hereof ("Grantor Leases") with respect to the land more particularly described on Exhibit B attached hereto and made a part hereof (the "Property") . B. Grantor desires to grant, convey and transfer to Grantee an easement and right-of-way for the erection, installation and maintenance of certain facilities for the transmission of electric power over and across a certain portion of the Property. IN CONSIDERATION of the foregoing and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged, the Parties agree as follows: 1. Grant. Grantor does hereby grant, convey and transfer to Grantee, a nonexclusive easement and right-of-way (the "Transmission Easement") one-hundred fifty (150) feet in width in, on, over, across, along and under that portion of the Property generally described on Exhibit C (the "Easement Area") attached hereto for the purposes of erecting, constructing, replacing, relocating, improving, enlarging, removing, maintaining, operating and utilizing, from time to time, a line or lines of towers and/or poles, with such wires and/or cables (whether above ground or buried), for the transmission of electrical energy, and all necessary and proper foundations, footings, cross arms and other appliances, facilities and fixtures for use in connection therewith including without limitation, vaults and junction boxes (whether above or below ground), manholes, handholes, conduit, fiber optics, cables, wires, lines and other conductors of any nature, multiple above or below ground control, communications, data and radio relay systems, and telecommunications equipment, including without limitation, conduit, fiber optics, cables, wires and lines (collectively, the "Transmission Facilities") in, on, over, across, along and under the Easement Area; together with the right of ingress to and egress from the Transmission Facilities by such persons, vehicles and equipment necessary for the above-described purposes over and along the Property. To the extent that Grantee determines that the Transmission Facilities cannot reasonably be located entirely within the Easement Area, Grantor agrees that it will not withhold its consent to such relocated Easement Area over the applicable portion of the Property and shall execute an amendment to this Agreement reflecting the amended Easement Area. 2. No Interference. Grantor covenants and agrees that it shall not construct, install, or permit to be constructed or installed, any improvements, fences, structures, buildings, foliage or vegetation, utility lines or other improvements of any type whatsoever upon or near the Easement Area which would inhibit or impair any of Grantee's rights or benefits as set forth in this Agreement. Grantee shall have the right, without compensation to Grantor, to cut, prune and remove or otherwise dispose of any foliage or vegetation on or near the Easement Area that Grantee deems a threat or potential threat to Grantee's Transmission Facilities or its rights hereunder. Grantor shall not grant or permit any person or person(s) claiming through Grantor, other than Grantee (but excluding [Tecolote Wind LLC][Duran Mesa LLC]), any right-of-way, encumbrance, easement, subeasement, or other right or interest in, to or affecting the Easement Area, without the prior written consent of Grantee in each instance, which consent Grantee may grant, withhold or deny in its sole, absolute and subjective discretion. 3. Construction of Transmission Facilities. Grantor acknowledges and agrees that during and in respect of the construction, installation, maintenance and repair of the Transmission Facilities in, over and through the Property, Grantee shall be entitled to access, occupy and use temporary staging and lay down areas within the Property reasonably proximate to the Easement Area. 4. Term. The term of this Agreement shall commence on the date this Agreement is executed and shall be for a term of the longer of (a) thirty (30) years and (b) the term of the Grantor Leases (the "Term"). 5. Authority. In the event that any deed of trust or other encumbrance that might interfere with Grantee's right to use the Property pursuant to this Transmission Easement is now or hereafter recorded against title to the Property in priority to this Transmission Easement (each, a "Prior Encumbrance"), Grantor covenants and agrees, at the request of Grantee, to use its best efforts to obtain from the holder of such Prior Encumbrance either: (a) an executed recordable subordination of such Prior Encumbrance to this Transmission Easement; or (b) an executed non-disturbance agreement or mutual co-existence agreement which is acceptable to Grantee, acting reasonably. 6. Indemnification and Insurance. Grantee shall maintain liability insurance insuring Grantee and Grantor against loss caused by Grantee's use of the Property. The amount of insurance shall be not less than $2,000,000.00 of combined single limit liability coverage. Grantee shall indemnify, defend, and hold Grantor harmless from and against any and all claims, liabilities, losses, costs, and expenses (including, without limitation, court costs and reasonable attorney's fees) of any nature which may be asserted against or incurred by Grantor to the extent caused by or arising out of the negligent acts or omissions or willful misconduct in the operations or activities on the Transmission Easement by the Grantee or its employees, agents, contractors, licensees, tenants and/or subtenants, or a breach of any obligation of Grantee under this Agreement, including specifically any and all environmental claims. Such indemnification shall survive the expiration or termination of this Agreement. 7. Grantee's Property. Notwithstanding that in constructing, maintaining and operating the Transmission Facilities, Grantee may install equipment and appurtenances in, on, over, along, under or across the Easement Area in such a manner that it or they become affixed to the Easement Area, the title to such equipment and appurtenances shall at all times remain the personal property of Grantee. 8. Assignment by Grantee; Mortgage Rights. (a) Right to Mortgage & Assign. Grantee, upon notice to Grantor, but without Grantor's consent or approval shall have the right to grant a deed of trust, mortgage, collaterally assign, or otherwise encumber and grant security interests in all or any part of its interest in this Transmission Easement or the Easement Area, or the Transmission Facilities (collectively, "Grantee's Assets"). These various security interests in all or a part of Grantee's Assets are collectively referred to as "Mortgages" and the holders of the Mortgages, their designees, successors and assigns are collectively referred to as "Mortgagees." Grantee's notice to Grantor shall include the name and address of each Mortgagee and/or Assignee (as defined below). Grantee shall also have the right, upon notice to Grantor, but without Grantor's consent or approval, to sell, convey, lease, or assign all or any portion of Grantee's Assets on either an exclusive or a non-exclusive basis, or to grant sub-easements, co-easements, separate easements, leases, licenses or similar rights, however denominated (collectively, "Assignment"), to one or more persons or entities (collectively, "Assignees"). Assignees and Mortgagees shall use Grantee's Assets only for the uses permitted under this Agreement. Assignees and Mortgagees shall have all rights and remedies allowed them under the existing laws except as limited by their individual agreements with Grantee, provided that under no circumstances shall any Mortgagee or Assignee have any greater rights of ownership or use of the Property than the rights granted to Grantee in this Agreement. (b) Grantor Obligations. Grantor agrees to consent in writing to and to execute customary financing documents, including customary three party lender agreements, as may reasonably be required by Mortgagees, at Grantee's sole cost. As a precondition to exercising any rights or remedies related to any alleged default by Grantee under this Agreement, Grantor shall give written notice of the default to each Mortgagee and Assignee at the same time it delivers notice of default to Grantee, specifying in detail the alleged event of default and the required remedy. Each Mortgagee and Assignee shall have the same amount of time to cure the default as to Grantee's entire interest or its partial interest in Grantee's Assets as is given to Grantee and the same right to cure any default as Grantee or to remove any property of Grantee, Mortgagees or Assignees located on the Easement Area. The cure period for each Mortgagee and Assignee shall begin to run at the end of the cure period given to Grantee in this Agreement, but in no case shall the cure period for any Mortgagee or Assignee be less than ninety (90) days after receipt of the default notice. Failure by Grantor to give a Mortgagee or Assignee notice of default shall not diminish Grantor's rights against Grantee, but shall preserve all rights of the Mortgagee or Assignee to cure any default and to remove any property of Grantee, the Mortgagee or Assignee located on the Easement Area. (c) Mortgagee/Assignee Obligations. Any Mortgagee or Assignee that does not directly hold an interest in Grantee's Assets, or whose interest is held solely for security purposes, shall have no obligation or liability under this Agreement prior to the time the Mortgagee or Assignee directly holds an interest in this Agreement, or succeeds to absolute title to Grantee's interest. A Mortgagee or Assignee shall be liable to perform obligations under this Agreement only for and during the period it directly holds such interest or absolute title. Any Assignment permitted under this Agreement shall release Grantee or other assignor from obligations accruing after the date that liability is assumed by the Assignee. (d) Right to Cure Defaults/Notice of Defaults/Right to New Transmission Easement. (1) To prevent termination of this Agreement, the Transmission Easement, or any partial interest in this Agreement and the Transmission Easement, Grantee, any Mortgagee or Assignee shall have the right, but not the obligation, at any time to perform any act necessary to cure any default and to prevent the termination of this Agreement or any interest in Grantee's Assets. (2) In the event of an uncured default by the holder of Grantee's entire interest in this Agreement, or in the event of a termination of this Agreement by agreement, by operation of law or otherwise, each Mortgagee or Assignee of a partial interest in Grantee's Assets that is not in material default of its obligations shall have the right to have Grantor either recognize the Mortgagee's or Assignee's interest or, in the event of a termination, grant new easements substantially identical to this Agreement and the Transmission Easement. Under the new easements, the Mortgagee or Assignee shall be entitled to, and Grantor shall not disturb, Mortgagee's or Assignee's continued use and enjoyment for the remainder of the Term, or such shorter term as an Assignee may otherwise be entitled pursuant to its Assignment. (e) Extended Cure Period. If any default by Grantee under this Agreement cannot be cured without obtaining possession of all or part of Grantee's Assets, then any such default shall be deemed remedied if a Mortgagee or Assignee: (a) within ninety (90) days after receiving notice from Grantor as set forth in Section 8(b), acquires possession of all or part of Grantee's Assets, or begins appropriate judicial or nonjudicial proceedings to obtain the same; (b) diligently prosecutes any such proceedings to completion; and (c) after gaining possession of all or part of Grantee's Assets cures defects that are reasonably capable of being cured and not otherwise personal to Grantor and performs all other obligations as and when the same are due in accordance with the terms of this Agreement. If a Mortgagee or Assignee is prohibited by any court or by operation of any bankruptcy or insolvency laws from commencing or prosecuting the proceedings described above, the ninety (90) day period specified above for commencing proceedings shall be extended for the period of such prohibition. (f) Certificates. Grantor shall promptly execute estoppel certificates (certifying as to truthful matters, including without limitation that no default then exists under this Agreement, if such be the case), consents to assignment, direct lender agreements and non-disturbance agreements as Grantee or any Mortgagee or Assignee may reasonably request from time to time. Grantor and Grantee shall cooperate in amending this Agreement from time to time to include any provision that may be reasonably requested by Grantee or any Mortgagee or Assignee to implement the provisions contained in this agreement or to preserve a Mortgagee's security interest in Grantee's Assets, in each case, at Grantee's expense. 9. Mortgagee Protection. Any Mortgagee, upon delivery to Grantor of notice of its name and address, for so long as its Mortgage is in existence shall be entitled to the following protections which shall be in addition to those granted elsewhere in this Agreement: (a) Mortgagee's Right to Possession, Right to Acquire and Right to Assign. A Mortgagee shall have the absolute right without Grantor's consent: (a) to assign its Mortgage; (b) to enforce its lien, including, to acquire title to all or any portion of Grantee's Assets by any lawful means; (c) to take possession of and operate all or any portion of Grantee's Assets and to perform all obligations to be performed by Grantee under this Agreement, or to cause a receiver or a receiver and manager to be appointed to do so; and (d) to acquire all or any portion of Grantee's Assets by foreclosure, by an assignment in lieu of foreclosure or by quit claim and thereafter without Grantor's consent to assign or transfer all or any portion of Grantee's Assets to a third party. Each Party shall from time to time and without cost to the other Parties promptly execute and deliver all further documents and take all additional actions necessary or appropriate to give effect to the provisions and intent hereof, including but not limited to such documents and actions as may be necessary or appropriate to reflect the assignment of the Common Facility Agreement in the real property records of Torrance County. 10. Amendment. No amendment or modification of this Assignment or any provision hereof shall be valid or effective unless in writing and signed by each of the Parties hereto. 11. Recording.
